name: Ash Way Park & Ride DRIVE THROUGH - COVID Vaccine Site
address: Ash Way Park & Ride DRIVE THROUGH: 16327 Ash Way, Lynnwood WA, 98087
info:
**THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC**
Starting May 13, 2021, everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, you must be 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine. Any minors receiving the vaccine will need a parent or guardian *physically present* to sign the consent form. 

Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
info: *** PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!***!!!!VACUNAS DE PFIZER!!! The vaccination clinic will take place at the Toppenish Rodeo Grounds. Masks are required. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via video/phone call or paper format. name: Olympic Pharmacy and Healthcare Services - COVID Vaccine Venue
address: 4700 Point Fosdick Drive, Suite 120, Gig Harbor WA, 98335
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS FOR JANSSEN (JOHNSON&JOHNSON) VACCINATIONS ONLY**
You must be 18 years of age or older.

Please bring your State ID, and if you have insurance, please bring your insurance card or Medicare B card (red, white and blue card).

Please do not come to the clinic if you are not feeling well.

Please wear loose sleeved, short sleeved or sleeveless shirt.

Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing.

Please be prepared to wait 15-30 minutes after vaccination for observation of adverse reactions.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp
address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a walk-in clinic at Capital Mall located at 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 12 and older from 12pm-8pm.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store.• All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
